        "virtue": "The Messenger of Allah ﷺ said, “When one of you sneezes, he should say [the above].” (Bukhārī 6224)\nThe Messenger of Allah ﷺ said, “Indeed Allah likes sneezing and dislikes yawning. So if someone sneezes and then praises Allah, then it is obligatory on every Muslim who heard him, to reply. As for yawning, it is from Shayṭān, so one must try one’s best to stop it. If one says ‘Hā’ when yawning, Shayṭān laughs at him.” (Bukhārī 6223)\nTwo men sneezed in the presence of the Prophet ﷺ. The Prophet ﷺ replied to one of them, but he did not reply to the other person. On being asked (why), the Prophet ﷺ said, “That one praised Allah (at the time of sneezing), while this one did not praise Allah.” (Bukhārī 6221)\nThe Messenger of Allah ﷺ said, “The rights of a Muslim on the Muslims are six.” It was said to him: “O Messenger of Allah ﷺ, what are they?” He replied: “When you meet him, greet him; when he invites you to a meal, accept it; when he seeks your advice, give him advice; when he sneezes and praises Allah, reply; when he falls ill, visit him; and when he dies, follow his funeral.” (Muslim 2162)",
